article.headline: Radford 77, Alcorn State 49
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Chris Oliver had 21 points and 14 rebounds, lifting Radford to a 77-49 win over Alcorn State Saturday night in the consolation game of the Florida International Tip-Off Tournament. Reggie McIntyre had 15 points and Amir Johnson added 14 for the Highlanders (1-4), who shot 44 percent from the field and held Alcorn State to 27 percent shooting. Jumane Reed scored 12 points for Alcorn State (0-5), which got 10 points from Juan Wyatt.
